<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by CarPd13m on 05-04-2002 07:39 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">First thing to say: NICE  :D

One thing that is so much better then other rpg's I played is the mood, Most of the other games have a very dark in the very beginning, they confront you immidiatly with great evil,  :Divinity: doesn't, maybe other RPG do also but I haven't played one yet.

Another thing is, the graphics may be 'outdated' cus they aren't 3D and so on, but who cares, who plays aa game only for it's good graphics? as long as they're not distractingly bad but :divinity: has amazingly great quality 2D graphics, very detailed as promised.

I don't think many hack&slashers would like the game, demo cus they always attack any enemy in sight, when they encounter a 'monster' too strong for them they won't like it (well most of them). also the combat is not that easy, wich i like it's more theb just klik klik klik klik klik klik ...

what woul be nice is a auto-save function.

as promised it is very interactive, the kitty, placing th flowers on jakes grave, needing to move packages to find secret's altough you can enter some of the while their are still object in the way by clicking on them.

how can you do multiple attack's again I tried to push the pause, and click on serveral enemies to atack, but when i clicked on one it automaticly unpuases en attacks, this is a bit anoying you should be able to unpause it yourself: "pause click to atack, whow I didn't see that i'll attack that one first unpause" something like that would be nicer, even if you pause to use some healing it unpuasess

It was worth downloading the 400 mb, it's a pitty you could use THE 1024 resolution.

their a lot more good things to say but you'll find many of them on the features page  :D

and again NIIIICE!  :D

------------------
1st Member of the divine fansite ownerz guild // [URL=http://www.angelfire.com/ego/divdev]The Divine Devotion[/URL]</TEXTAREA>
